item.description:
arXiv:2407.12157v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: Having in mind the significance of parity (reflection) in various areas of physics, the single-mode and two-mode Wigner algebras are considered adding to them a reflection operator. The associated deformed $su(2)$ algebra, $su_{
u}(2)$, and the deformed $so(3)$ algebra, $so_{
u}(3)$, are constructed for the widely used Jordan-Schwinger and Holstein-Primakoff realizations, commenting on various aspects and ingredients of the formalism for both single-mode and two-mode cases. Finally, in this framework the parity-deformed $so_{
u}(3)$ representation is analyzed, due to its potential application in the study of qubit and qutrit systems.
